    "created_at": "2016-03-15T07:31:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-15T07:31:49Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Mmh, I'd suggest catching that import of `backports.shutil_get_terminal_size` and issuing a clearer message. Given that the name of that module carries a dot in it, it's really confusing: I spent some time tracking down the problem down to this PR (much like @Achifaifa), before realizing that I wasn't missing some module called `backports`, but instead that someone literally decided to name a package with a dot in it!!  \n\nI guess there's nothing we can do about that (I think it's unnecessarily confusing to users, imagine if people start making lots of top-level packages with dots in their names, the fun we're going to have tracking down import errors).  But at least we can mitigate it via a message, given this is such a special case.\n\nJust my 2 cents...\n"
  },
