    "created_at": "2016-03-15T10:09:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-15T10:09:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yep, it's only an issue for people updating from git - anyone installing a released version, or even installing afresh from git, will get it automatically.\n\nWe've been down the road of trying to add better error messages before (with jsonschema), and it later ended up obscuring a problem with jsonschema's dependency specifications, because there was an `ImportError` coming from some other package. I don't think we should try to be clever with this - having to deal with new dependencies occasionally is an occupational hazard of living on master. Maybe we should ping them mailing list to let people know what they need to install, but I don't think it needs changes to the code itself.\n"
